race.comment: TRIANNA (4) worked into the race nicely here 4 weeks ago over this trip, and dug deep to finish runner-up by a short head. She is racing out of her rightful maiden class, but this field is no harder than her last race, and she can go one better. BONNIE GEM (3) has been freshened up since finishing runner-up by a short head on this track nearly 6 weeks ago. She is likely to be ridden positively again and will be among the hardest to beat. ASPARK PARK (2) made up some solid late ground when finishing third here 12 days ago, and he will be peaking at the right time here. He has a better draw and is a must for all top 4 combinations. RARAWA RAY (6) has had plenty of experience at the trials and won his latest at Avondale last month. He has picked a nice race to make his debut, and any market support is worth following. DON PAULY (1) is resuming at the right level for him, and if right, he can give this a big shake. SHATIN (5) is better than his form suggests. Don't drop him.
